Parses argv and dispatches into the `runner` module, which handles the actual backlog mutations and renders. The CLI surface is: `list` (print priority-sorted backlog), `add-task` (append a row), `delete-task` (remove by id), and two hidden commands (`migrate` from markdown, `render` from store).

The `list` output prepends each row with its id — a handle for `delete-task` — but `docs/STATUS.md` itself never shows ids; its 4-column shape is shared with `ctx-brief`. The id column is purely a CLI affordance.

`dispatch(fs, cli, out)` is the entry point: it resolves store/view paths from flags (defaulting to `docs/status.json` and `docs/STATUS.md`), pattern-matches the subcommand, and delegates to `runner::{list, add_task, delete_task, migrate, render}`. All I/O failures go through `StatusError::Io`; stdout writes are caught and tagged as `<stdout>`.